        <IsA>app:gui</IsA>
        <Summary>Wireless configuration tool</Summary>
        <Description>Gtk+2 utility for Linux that helps you configure your wireless devices. Although primarily written for the rt2x00 project, it supports any Linux wireless extensions compliant kernel module. For now, if you want to use WPA on ralink based wireless devices, you need to either manually set the parameters from console or use this frontend. To access to network you need to setup a profile and activate it from the icon in the panel. You can scan for access-points from the site survey menu.</Description>
